# This project USES Git (ignore the old filename)

**The file name `no-github-railway-deploy` is misleading and historical.** **Lumo 22 uses Git for version control and for normal redeploys.**

**When the user asks to deploy, redeploy, ship, or commit:** use **`git status`** → **`git add`** → **`git commit`** → **`git push`** to the branch Railway watches (usually **`main`**). That push is the **default** production deploy.

**Do not** use **`railway up`** as the default. Use the Railway CLI upload **only** if the user **explicitly** asks for it, GitHub is not connected to Railway, or they need a one-off without pushing.

**Full detail:** **`.cursor/rules/railway-deploy.mdc`** (canonical; same policy as this file).
